No, not in this particular case.

There&#39;s nothing inherently wrong about statements like &quot;the semantics
of POST requests vary for different resources&quot;. The key is that those
varying semantics are _not visible_ on the network and are derived
only from the shared understanding between client and server. That&#39;s
not a violation of REST constraints or the HTTP spec, it&#39;s a small
clarification.

I definitely agree though, there are some REST constraints and
concepts that are misused. This seems to happen frequently with terms
like &#39;visibility&#39; and &#39;self-descriptive&#39; :)

Cheers,
